# Application Structure (app/)

The `app/` directory contains the core application logic, likely built using a framework like FastAPI.

- **Entry Point:** [app/main.py](mdc:app/main.py) initializes the application.
- **Database:**
    - Connection and session logic: [app/database.py](mdc:app/database.py)
    - Database models (ORM): [app/models/](mdc:app/models)
    - CRUD operations: [app/crud/](mdc:app/crud)
- **API & Schemas:**
    - Pydantic schemas: [app/schemas/](mdc:app/schemas) and/or [app/schemas.py](mdc:app/schemas.py)
    - GraphQL endpoint implementation: [app/graphql/](mdc:app/graphql)
- **Business Logic:** [app/services/](mdc:app/services)
- **Authentication/Authorization:** [app/auth/](mdc:app/auth)
- **Core Configuration/Utilities:** [app/core/](mdc:app/core)
- **Logging:** Configuration in [app/logging_config.py](mdc:app/logging_config.py)
- **Agents:** Specialized logic in [app/agents/](mdc:app/agents)
